Jon,

I agree in principle, but  what happens if another member of your
family get their mail service from another provider?

How about something like:  mailbox@jon.postel.mdr.ca.us

with an MX of

jon.postel.mdr.ca.us     MX     mci-mail.com

Where the (automatic" reciepient of "mailbox" on that host knows
enough to read the whole name and send the thing to the right
person?  This should be easy enough to implement as a unix mail filter...

Mike

